            <paragraph>The visual layers to account for when baking for occluders. Only <reference internal="True" refuri="class_meshinstance3d#class-meshinstance3d"><inline classes="std std-ref">MeshInstance3D</inline></reference>s whose <reference internal="True" refuri="class_visualinstance3d#class-visualinstance3d-property-layers"><inline classes="std std-ref">VisualInstance3D.layers</inline></reference> match with this <reference internal="True" refid="class-occluderinstance3d-property-bake-mask"><inline classes="std std-ref">bake_mask</inline></reference> will be included in the generated occluder mesh. By default, all objects with <emphasis>opaque</emphasis> materials are taken into account for the occluder baking.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>To improve performance and avoid artifacts, it is recommended to exclude dynamic objects, small objects and fixtures from the baking process by moving them to a separate visual layer and excluding this layer in <reference internal="True" refid="class-occluderinstance3d-property-bake-mask"><inline classes="std std-ref">bake_mask</inline></reference>.</paragraph>
